Head Office and Technology Centers




						> About Us / 
						Head Office and Technology Centers /
					


	Hong Kong Head Office Technology Center

	The Group's Head Office Technology Center ("head office") is in ultra-modern premises at the Hong Kong Science Park, strategically sited near core suppliers and on the doorstep of the global market. The head office includes management offices, corporate development and communications department, technology center for IC design and product development, quality and logistics management department, sales and marketing team, customer services, finance, HR, IT, and office administration.


	Solomon Systech has an in-house specialized laboratory equipped with advanced design, development and testing equipments that support complete IC design, product development, product qualification and test development of its specialized Mixed Mode High Voltage System-On-Chip (HV-SoC) and VLSI design capabilities.

	 

	The technology centre in Hong Kong collaborates closely with the technology center in Shenzhen in product R&D given the geographical proximity.    



	 

	Nanjing Technology Center (Solomon Systech (China) Limited)

	The Group established the Nanjing Technology Center (“NJTC”), i.e. Solomon Systech (China) Limited, in November 2017 as a strategic step to further enhancing its presence and visibility in China, strengthening relationships with key customers, and also enhancing the overall technological capability to foster innovation. This marks an important milestone for its future expansion in China.

	Located in Nanjing Jiangbei New District, the NJTC occupies two floors. It could hold up to 200 employees, with a spacious, well-equipped R&D lab. The NJTC has full-fledged capability from business development and marketing, IC design, research and product development, to providing on-site support including application design, software design, quality control and logistic services to local and transnational customers.
	 



	 

	Shenzhen Technology Center

	The Shenzhen Technology Center (SZTC) was established in 2000 with a view to expanding the Group's business and investment in China. SZTC has full-fledged product development capabilities including marketing, IC design, product engineering, quality and manufacturing, sales and field application.

	 

 

	 

	Taiwan Technology Center

	Solomon Systech further strengthens its presence in the region with the establishment of the Taiwan Technology Centre ("TWTC") in January 2017 in Hsinchu City of Taiwan. The TWTC is strategically located in close proximity to key customers and business partners. It aims to further enhance rapport with key customers and business partners, and also to utilize the local technical expertise to further strengthen technological capability and the pace of innovation of the Group.

	 



	 

	UK Technology Center

	Subsequent to the purchase of advanced mobile touch technology assets and semiconductor products from Microchip Technology Incorporated in November 2016, Solomon Systech established the UK Technology Centre ("UKTC") to focus on the R&D, and sales & marketing of the innovative and high-performance mobile touch products, in particular maXTouch® semiconductor products. The UKTC also collaborates closely with the other Solomon Systech business & technology centres in the region to develop new touch products and to drive business growth.

	 



	 

	Korea Technology Center

	Solomon Systech further strengthens its presence in the region and also enhances its technology capability with the establishment of the Korea Technology Centre ("KRTC") in April 2017.

	 



	 








